  "prompt": "What are some words that are the opposite of include?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are some words that are opposite in meaning to \"include\":\n\n1. **Exclude**\n   - **Definition:** To deliberately leave something or someone out.\n   - **Example:** The event will exclude attendees under the age of 18.\n\n2. **Omit**\n   - **Definition:** To leave out or fail to include something.\n   - **Example:** Please omit the last chapter from the report.\n\n3. **Leave Out**\n   - **Definition:** Similar to omit; to not include something.\n   - **Example:** She decided to leave out unnecessary details from her presentation.\n\n4. **Remove**\n   - **Definition:** To take something away or eliminate it.\n   - **Example:** They decided to remove outdated information from the website.\n\n5. **Except**\n   - **Definition:** Not including; other than.\n   - **Example:** Everyone is invited except John.\n\n6. **Reject**\n   - **Definition:** To refuse to accept or include something.\n   - **Example:** The committee chose to reject the proposal.\n\n7. **Eliminate**\n   - **Definition:** To completely remove or get rid of something.\n   - **Example:** The goal is to eliminate errors from the manufacturing process.\n\n8. **Restrict**\n   - **Definition:** To limit or control what is included.\n   - **Example:** The diet restricts the intake of sugary foods.\n\nThese antonyms can be used in various contexts depending on the specific meaning you want to convey opposite to \"include.\"",
